>>>>>>> The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) is
responsible for producing guidelines for use by healthcare professionals about
the care people with diabetes should receive. As part of the process of
developing guidelines, NICE consults with organisations such as Diabetes UK.
This is an opportunity to comment on the guidelines and evidence, to raise
issues of relevance which impact on the quality of care and quality of life
